ANTHRAX, HUMAN, HIPPOPOTAMUS - ZAMBIA (02): (EASTERN PROVINCE)
**************************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 5 Sep 2011
Source: MUVI Television [edited]
http://www.muvitv.com/?p=19617


Chama anthrax cases increase
----------------------------
Anthrax cases in Chama District, Eastern Province, have increased to
205 since the disease outbreak on 26 Aug 2011. Ministry of Health
Acting spokesperson, Maximillian Bweupe, says 80 cases have been
recorded since last week.

Dr Bweupe has explained to MUVI TV that the disease is suspected to
have been transmitted from hippos in the Luangwa River. He has further
said that the ministry has set a task force to deal with the
situation.

